&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THE ROLE&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;📝&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity to join Form3&#39;s growing US Product team as a Senior Product Manager, helping shape our US Account-to-Account (A2A) payments proposition.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&#39;ll own products across the full lifecycle, from discovery and strategy through to delivery, launch, and commercialisation. While you&#39;ll contribute across our US A2A portfolio, your initial focus will be on building and scaling new payment capabilities, particularly Wire and ACH and supporting existing capability like RTP and FedNow.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and execute the product strategy and roadmap for your US payment products, delivering measurable customer and commercial outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bring new payment capabilities to market, leading products from discovery through launch and ongoing optimisation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Engineering and Business Analysis to deliver scalable, high-quality products that meet customer and market needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build strong relationships with banks and financial institutions to uncover customer challenges and translate them into valuable product capabilities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enable commercial success by supporting customer engagements, go-to-market initiatives and strategic sales opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Shape product pricing, positioning and competitive differentiation to maximise market adoption.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure products remain compliant, competitive and aligned with evolving payment scheme and regulatory requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work collaboratively across Product, Engineering and Commercial teams to deliver exceptional customer experiences and business growth.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WE ARE LOOKING FOR&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;🔍&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for a Senior Product Manager with experience building account-to-account payment products for banks and financial institutions. You&#39;ll combine deep knowledge of the US payments landscape with strong product leadership, commercial acumen and the ability to deliver products that solve customer problems and drive business growth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years&#39; Product Management experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong knowledge of the US account-to-account payments landscape, in particular Wire, ACH and ideally RTP/FedNow.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience building products for banks or financial institutions, either within a bank or a technology provider.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to take products from concept through launch and into live operation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong commercial mindset, with experience supporting pricing, go-to-market strategy and customer engagement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of the competitive landscape for payment infrastructure,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable working closely with Engineering to translate customer needs into scalable products.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent stakeholder management and communication skills, with the ability to influence across technical and commercial teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Desirable:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience building API-first and cloud-native products.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Has worked in a high-growth startup or scaleup environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
